Hon. Kehinde Odeneye, House of Representatives member representing Ijebu Ode/Odogbolu/Ijebu North-East Federal Constituency in the National Assembly, Abuja has called on Yoruba youths to harness their thoughts and be well positioned in order to take the mantle of leadership. Speaking at an event held in Arepo community in Ogun State on Monday where he was recognized as Yoruba Royal Icon and presented with the Advisory Royal Patron award by the Yoruba Council of Youths Worldwide (YCYW), he tasked youths in the Southwest region restrategize for the great task of leadership ahead. Appreciating the council for the recognition and award conferred on him, Hon. Odeneye assured YCYW of his continued support for the group and interest of the Yoruba race within the country and in other parts of the world. He advised the council to be more engaged in national issues, mass mobilization of its activities and engagement of youths in creative ventures using the thriving entertainment platform to woe the attention of youths for gainful trades, saying that adoption of a popular Nollywood personality as ambassador would bring the council into the reckoning. Earlier, Aremo (Barr.) Oladotun Hassan, YCYW President, said the award bestowed on Hon. Odeneye was in recognition of his exemplary humanitarian programmes and other laudable gestures within and beyond his constituency. He urged the award recipient not to relent in its activities as a worthy representative of his constituency and promotion of the Yoruba race common interest and aspirations in the scheme of things in the country. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.